OL,3,CLabour and Tories have pledged not to
OL,4,Craise taxes - but do their plans add
OL,5,Cup?
OL,7,FThese cuts will hit investment
OL,8,Fspending to build and hospitals, and
OL,9,Fspending on day-to-day public services.
OL,11,FSpending on areas like the NHS,
OL,12,Fschools, defence and childcare is
OL,13,Flikely to be protected - which leaves
OL,14,Funprotected areas vulnerable.
OL,16,FCouncils have already gone bust,
OL,17,Fprisons are full, courts are clogged
OL,18,Fwith cases and are increasingly
OL,19,Fstruggling - and no party has told us
OL,20,Fwhere cuts can be made.
