OL,3,CLabour and Tories have pledged not to
OL,4,Craise taxes - but do their plans add
OL,5,Cup?
OL,7,FInstead, the hope appears to be that
OL,8,Fwhoever forms the next government will
OL,9,Fsuddenly be dealt a set of aces.
OL,11,FThese could be a slump in the price of
OL,12,Foil and gas, big cuts in interest
OL,13,Frates, an economic boom - the
OL,14,Fdiscovery of vast reserves of lithium
OL,15,Fin , perhaps.
OL,17,FThe next government may get incredibly
OL,18,Flucky. But if these things don't
OL,19,Fhappen, then voters are in for an
OL,20,Funpleasant surprise after the election.
